name: Why Not
description: Vienna's oldest and most iconic gay nightclub, operating since the 1980s. Features three floors with different music styles (pop, house, electronic), three bars, and regular themed parties and drag shows. A staple of Vienna's LGBTQ+ nightlife scene.

name: Felixx
description: Chic LGBTQ+-friendly cocktail bar in Mariahilf district. Known for stylish decor with elaborate chandelier, creative cocktails, and welcoming atmosphere. Hosts themed nights, karaoke, happy hours, and regular events for the queer community.

name: Village Bar
description: Popular trendy gay bar in the heart of Naschmarkt gay district. Features retro vibe with modern flair, strong community atmosphere, and hosts after-parties for major LGBTQ+ events like Pride Festival and Rainbow Ball.

name: Marea Alta
description: Queer bar originally founded to promote lesbian immigrants and lesbian visibility. Features 'Open Minded' neon sign, hosts karaoke nights, drag shows, and regular LGBTQ+ events. Open Monday-Thursday 18:00-02:00, Friday-Saturday 19:00-04:00.

name: Titanic (Pitbull Vienna)
description: Historic gay club established in 1982, especially popular with bears, leather lovers, and butch aesthetics. Underground club specializing in masculine-themed parties with bold, unapologetic atmosphere and body-positive environment.

name: Mango Bar
description: Popular gay bar in Naschmarkt district, operating since 1981. Known for regular events, drink specials, young lively crowd, private outdoor space, and designated smoking area. Hosts themed nights and DJ events.

name: Gugg
description: Community café and cultural center run by HOSI Wien (Austria's oldest LGBTQ+ organization). Hosts talks, film screenings, cultural events, and casual gatherings. Cozy inclusive space for queer activism and community building.

name: Rosa Lila Villa
description: Iconic LGBTQ+ community center and cornerstone for lesbian visibility since 1982. Historic painted building serving as cultural and political hub for queer activism, safe spaces, and community events. Houses multiple organizations including Villa Vida café.

name: Villa Vida
description: Queer community café opened in 2019 within Rosa Lila Villa. Welcoming space for celebration, food, drinks, and community gatherings. Focuses on creating inclusive environment for LGBTQ+ individuals and allies.

name: Eagle Vienna
description: Venue for leather and fetish subculture within the gay community. Primarily a cruising bar that hosts specific events and themed nights catering to the leather, bear, and fetish scene.
